        Returns:

      • moveToTableau

        public boolean moveToTableau(Card card,
                             int pile)
        "moveToTableau" method moves the card to the column pile (parameter). The card's position in the game will be searched and once found, the card will be popped from its position and will be checked if is is valid to move the card/top card (with the other cards) to the column pile (parameter). Public access.
        Parameters:
        card - (parameter) of type Card is the card/top card to be moved.
        pile - (parameter) of type integer is the column number in which the card/top card to be put.
        Returns:
        this method returns true if the card/top card (with the other cards) was moved successfully and false if not.

      • getFromTableau

        public LinkedStack getFromTableau(int pile,
                                  int numberOfCards)
        "getFromTableau" method gets a number of cards in a pile. Public access.
        Parameters:
        pile - (parameter) of type Integer is the pile number where the card/s that is/are going to be moved located.
        numberOfCards - (paramter) of type integer is the number of how many cards the program will get.
        Returns:

      • loadGame

        public boolean loadGame(java.lang.String filename)
                 throws java.lang.Exception
        "loadGame" method loads a game state with the data from a file with the name filename (parameter). Public access.
        Parameters:
        filename - (parameter) of type String is the name of the file to be accessed where the data for the game state will be gathered.
        Returns:
        this method returns true if the game state was succcessfully loaded, false if not. (null == filename or filename is not found)
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - it throws mainly FileNotFoundException

      • saveGame

        public boolean saveGame(java.lang.String filename,
                        LinkedStack moveStockCards,
                        int noStock,
                        int noTalon)
                 throws java.lang.Exception
        "saveGame" method saves the current game state into a file with the name filename (parameter) . Public access.
        Parameters:
        filename - (parameter) of type String is the filename of the text file where the game states will be saved.
        moveStockCards - (parameter) of type LinkedStack is a linked list of cards of the talon pile from main that is needed for saving.
        noStock - (parameter) of type integer is the number that indicates the number of cards in the stock pile currently, used only in main. Needed for saving.
        noTalon - (parameter) of type integer is the number that indicates the number of cards in the talon pile currently, used only in main, Needed for saving.
        Returns:
        this method returns true if the game state was successfully saved and false if not. (the filename is new and there are 5 slots already).
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - it throws mainly FileNotFoundException

      • getCard

        public java.awt.image.BufferedImage getCard(int stack,
                                            int index)
        "getCard" method gets the BufferedImage card of the Card object in the corresponding index and stack.
        Parameters:
        stack - of int type tells what stack is to be accessed, 0 - null, 1 - stock, 2 - talon, 3 - foundations, 4 - tableau.
        index - of int type tells what index in stack is to be accesed. In cases of accesing in foundation and tableau stack, increments of 100 is for the representation of a specific pile in the stacks and increments of 1 for the card object itself.
        Returns:
        a bufferedimage is returned that corresponds to the card object accessed.
